    {
      "id": "PopularPost13302",
      "post_content": "I love this guy. I have a fairly straightforward beatdown deck (same colours as the Wurm here) and I use this guy to get some of my more useful cards back. One of my main strategies is to play Prized Unicorn, give him Gorgon's Flail (+1/+1 and deathtouch), and then attack (and maybe power him up with Giant Growth). Wipe out the opposing creatures, attack with Charnelhoard Wurm, get Prized Unicorn back, and repeat. He's slightly expensive, but I don't see why seven mana has to be a gamewinner so that doesn't bother me in the least. His effect makes up for it, I think.  \n  \nEDIT: You ever take a look at opinions you held years ago, and wonder what you were thinking? Finding this comment has been one of those moments for me. ",
      "posted_by": "SocialExperiment",
